                Turn them all on, and you've got complete visibility."
            </div>
        </div>
    )
}

# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

This is a single-file, standalone marketing website for "Genius AI" - an interactive showcase of 8 AI agents designed for automotive dealerships. The entire application is contained in `index.html` with no build process, dependencies, or backend.

## Technology Stack

- **React 18** (loaded via CDN from unpkg.com)
- **Babel Standalone** (for in-browser JSX transformation)
- Pure HTML5/CSS3 with inline styles
- Custom SVG icon components (simplified Lucide React icons)

## Running the Application

Simply open `index.html` in any web browser:
```bash
open index.html
```

No build step, no dependencies, no server required.

## Architecture

### Single Component Structure
The entire app is one React component: `GeniusAICampaign`

**State Management:**
- `activeAgents` - Set data structure tracking which of the 8 agents are "activated"
- Agent activation is toggled by clicking cards

**Three Visual States:**
1. **Inactive** (0 agents) - Gray theme
2. **Partial** (1-7 agents) - Purple/teal gradient theme
3. **Full Genius** (8 agents) - Gold theme with enhanced animations

### Agent Configuration
8 agents defined in array with properties:
- `id` - unique identifier
- `name` - display name
- `icon` - React component (custom SVG)
- `color` - theme color (purple #8B5CF6, teal #14B8A6, or indigo #6366F1)
- `description` - one-line description

### Key Features
- **Animated Atom Logo** - SVG with 3 rotating orbital rings that fill progressively as agents activate
- **Progress Bar** - Visual indicator of activation percentage
- **Interactive Cards** - Hover effects, click to toggle, dynamic borders/shadows
- **Conditional Styling** - Extensive use of ternary operators for state-based styling

## Styling Approach

**All styles are inline** - no external CSS files.

**Theme Colors:**
- Backgrounds: Dark navy/slate (`#0f172a`, `#1e293b`, `#334155`)
- Purple agents: `#8B5CF6` (Marketing, BDC, Lead Gen)
- Teal agents: `#14B8A6` (Sales, Service, Inventory)
- Indigo agents: `#6366F1` (Reporting, Predictive Desking)
- Gold "Full Genius": `#fbbf24`, `#f59e0b`

**Important Browser Compatibility Note:**
- Gradient text effects (`background-clip: text`) are NOT used due to browser compatibility issues
- Use solid colors with `textShadow` for glow effects instead
- Always provide fallback `color` property to ensure text visibility

## Common Modifications

### Adding a New Agent
1. Add new icon component if needed (follow existing SVG pattern)
2. Add agent object to `agents` array
3. Update agent count reference (currently 8) if showing counts

### Changing Colors
- Agent colors defined in `agents` array `color` property
- Gold theme colors hardcoded in conditional rendering (search for `#fbbf24`)
- Background gradients use multiple color stops - update consistently

### Modifying Animations
- Atom rotation: controlled by `@keyframes rotate` in inline `<style>` tag
- Pulse effect: `@keyframes pulse` for glow when all agents active
- Transition speeds: typically `0.3s` or `0.5s` ease

## File Structure

```
Agents-Site/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.html (entire application)
```

## Deployment

Copy `index.html` to any static hosting service. No build or compilation required.

# Framer Integration Instructions

This guide explains how to integrate your Genius AI campaign into Framer using the `framer-version.jsx` file.

## What Changed from the Original

The Framer version has been modified to work within Framer's React environment:

‚úÖ **Removed:**
- React/ReactDOM CDN script tags (Framer has React built-in)
- Babel Standalone script (Framer compiles JSX automatically)
- HTML boilerplate (head, body tags)

‚úÖ **Converted:**
- JSX to proper ES6 module format
- Added proper `import` statement for React hooks
- Exported component as `default export`
- Moved inline `<style>` tag to component-level styles

## Integration Steps

### Option 1: Code Component (Recommended)

This option provides the best integration with Framer and allows your component to work seamlessly with the rest of your site.

1. **Open your Framer project**
   - Go to your Framer project in the browser

2. **Insert a Code Component**
   - Click the **"+"** button in the left sidebar
   - Select **"Code"** from the menu
   - Choose **"New Component"**

3. **Copy the Component Code**
   - Open `framer-version.jsx` from your project folder
   - Copy the **entire contents** of the file
   - Paste it into Framer's code editor

4. **Add the Montserrat Font**
   - In your Framer project, go to **Settings** (gear icon)
   - Navigate to **"Fonts"** tab
   - Add **Google Fonts: Montserrat**
   - Select weights: 300, 400, 600, 700, 800

5. **Add Component to Canvas**
   - The component will appear in your Assets panel as "GeniusAICampaign"
   - Drag it onto your canvas
   - Resize to fit your page (recommended: full width)

6. **Configure Component Size**
   - Set width to **100%** or your desired container width
   - Height will adjust automatically based on content

### Option 2: Embed as iframe (Simpler, but Limited)

If you prefer to keep using the original HTML file:

1. **Host the HTML file**
   - Upload `index.html` to a hosting service (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages, etc.)
   - Get the public URL

2. **Add Embed Component in Framer**
   - In Framer, insert an **"Embed"** component from the Insert menu
   - Paste this code:
   ```html
   <iframe
     src="YOUR_HOSTED_URL_HERE"
     width="100%"
     height="1200px"
     frameborder="0"
     style="border: none;"
   ></iframe>
   ```

3. **Adjust iframe height** as needed to prevent scrolling

‚ö†Ô∏è **Note:** The iframe approach is less flexible and won't integrate as smoothly with your Framer site's design system.

## Customization Tips

### Change the Number of Agents

The current version shows **3 agents** (Marketing, Inventory, Reporting). To add more:

1. Import additional icons from the top of the file (or create your own)
2. Add new agent objects to the `agents` array:
   ```javascript
   const agents = [
       // ... existing agents
       {
           id: 'new-agent',
           name: 'New Agent',
           icon: YourIcon,
           color: '#YOUR_HEX_COLOR',
           description: 'Your description'
       }
   ]
   ```

### Modify Colors

**Agent Colors:**
- Purple: `#8B5CF6`
- Teal: `#14B8A6`
- Indigo: `#6366F1`

**Gold Theme (Full Genius):**
- Primary: `#fbbf24`
- Secondary: `#f59e0b`

Find and replace these hex codes throughout the component to customize.

### Adjust Animations

**Animation speeds** are defined in the `@keyframes` section:
- Pulse effect: `2s` (line with `animation: 'pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite'`)
- Ring rotations: `20s`, `15s`, `25s` (in the SVG `<g>` tags)

## Troubleshooting

### Component doesn't appear
- Make sure you copied the **entire file** including the `import` statement
- Check that the component is exported as `export default function`

### Fonts look wrong
- Verify Montserrat is added to your Framer project fonts
- The component uses a font-family fallback chain, so it will still work without Montserrat

### Animations not working
- Ensure the `<style>` tag with `@keyframes` is inside the component's return statement
- Check browser console for any errors

### SVG gradient IDs conflict
- If you have multiple instances of this component on the same page, the gradient IDs might conflict
- Make each ID unique by adding a suffix: `id="atomGradient-1"`, `id="atomGradient-2"`, etc.

